  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">William Lloyd Garrison received two letters from Oliver Johnson about Mrs. Oliver Johnson&apos;s great physical suffering and the hopelessness of her case. Garrison feels that death is a &quot;joyful liberation of the spirit from its clayey tenement.&quot; Garrison is suffering from &quot;spinal weakness and inflammation.&quot; He hasn&apos;t yet decided whether he will go to the Progressive Friends&apos; meeting in Longwood, Pennsylvania. Mrs. Mary Ashton Livermore will be one of the speakers at the meeting.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Accompanied by an envelope addressed to Oliver Johnson, Tribune Office, New York City.</subfield>
